Through to Dickson [Dicksons] Fjord.

Kjerulfs [Kjerulf] Fjord. Through to Dickson [Dicksons] Fjord. High point I reached at 4:55 PM on southern terminal range of mountains which had formed eastern side of Kjerulfs [Kjerulf] Fjord. Below me a fjord -- later proved to be Dickson [Dicksons];
properties.Desc2: the large glacier in Unknown Valley and Scoop Mt. [Mountain] clearly in view and the glacier passing N.E. around L.A.B.'s Scoop Mt. [Mountain] ended now in the Fjord below me.  See photos: 27-1-21; 26 H-8 & 26-H-9  Photo taken looking N.N.E.

properties.Desc_: Kjerulfs [Kjerulf] Fjord. Through to Dickson [Dicksons] Fjord.  High point:  I reached at 4:55 p.m. on southern terminal of range of mountains which had formed eastern side of Kjerulfs [Kjerulf] Fjord.  Below me a fjord --
properties.Desc2: later proved to be Dickson [Dicksons]--with the large glacier in Unknown Valley and my Scoop Mt. [Mountain] still clearly in view and the glacier passing around my Scoop Mt. [Mountain] ended now in the fjord below me.  In background: Mt. [mountain]
properties.Desc3: range with ice-cap (which was the continuance of my Scoop Mt. [Mountain] range) forming the south side of Dickson [Dicksons] Fjord and this was the furthest point E.N.E. that I could see.

properties.Desc_: Kjerulfs [Kjerulf] Fjord. Extreme inner end. In background on left southern terminal of range of mountains forming eastern side of Kjerulfs [Kjerulf] Fjord. From here mountains curve E.N.E. and form north side of Dickson [Dicksons] Fjord. On right side
properties.Desc2: of background is L.A.B.'s Scoop Mt. [Mountain] very abrupt side facing N.N.W. Scoop Mt. [Mountain] and the range to which it belongs form the eastern side of Unknown Valley (direction north and south or N.E. and S.W.) and show here as the mountains turn
properties.Desc3: N.N.E. and become the south side of Dickson [Dicksons] Fjord. At the base of the mountains is Hisinger Glacier [Hisinger Gletscher], filling the entire width of Unknown Valley, as it comes from the S.S.W. and here - at what can be called The Divide (see
properties.Desc4: photos 26-H-18; 26-H-15; 26-H-20; 27-1-18) passes N.E.E. around the base of Scoop Mt. [Mountain] and in a steep decline goes into Dickson [Dicksons] Fjord. (See photos 27-1-21 and 27-1-22) Where the glacier and the southern terminal of the eastern range
properties.Desc5: of Kjerulfs [Kjerulf] Fjord meet, the waters off the glacier go down along the side of the glacier to Dickson [Dicksons] Fjord; they also make a stream which descends through Left Valley and, passing out the Main Valley, goes into Kjerulfs [Kjerulf]
properties.Desc6: Fjord. See photos 27-1-13; 27-1-14 & 24-F-13. The entire Left Valley and stream descending it are shown. In foreground pool, on north side of Right Valley near eastern terminal. This pool was on a steep hillside above the stream and, from my higher
properties.Desc7: elevation, gave the impression of having been attached to or built on the mountain. Below it is stream of Right Valley near its mouth. Photo taken from high land just west of Cairn D., which I erected of stones on the southern terminal of range of
properties.Desc8: mountains forming the west side of Kjerulfs [Kjerulf] Fjord.

properties.Desc_: Kjerulfs [Kjerulf] Fjord. L.A.B.'s Curry-comb Peak, near extreme inner (southern) end of Left Valley; grooved sides form west side of Left Valley.  In foreground shallow pond-like lake which is source of stream of Left Valley, flowing
properties.Desc2: from this point down Left Valley to its mouth at junction of Left, Main and Right Valleys.  See photos 24-F-5; 24-F-13; 27-F-12. This is no. 6 in pan D
